Pope Francis (File: AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cairo - Egypt says Pope Francis will pay an official visit to the majority Muslim nation during the final week of April.Presidential spokesperson Alaa Youssef said on Saturday the Pope's visit will be in response to an invitation extended by President Abdel-Fattah al-Sisi, who met the Pope when he visited the Vatican in late 2014.Youssef says Francis will meet Sisi, as well as Egypt's top Muslim cleric, Sheikh Ahmed al-Tayeb, and Pope Tawadros II, the spiritual leader of Egypt's Coptic Christians.He says Egypt hopes the visit will cement the "spirit of tolerance and dialogue" between followers of different faiths and further isolate extremism and terrorism.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.